      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the results for **\"Language Models Represent Space and Time\"** by Wes Gurnee and Max Tegmark, published at ICLR 2024:\n\n## Overview\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This paper is part of the International Conference on Learning Representations 2024 (ICLR 2024) Conference."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " The authors are **Wes Gurnee** and **Max Tegmark**, and the paper is available on [arXiv (2310.02207)](https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.02207), [OpenReview](https://openreview.net/forum?id=jE8xbmvFin), and the [ICLR proceedings](https://proceedings.iclr.cc/paper_files/paper/2024/hash/0a6059857ae5c82ea9726ee9282a7145-Abstract-Conference.html).\n\n## Key Findings\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The capabilities of large language models (LLMs) have sparked debate over whether such systems just learn an enormous collection of superficial statistics or a set of more coherent and grounded representations that reflect the real world."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors find evidence for the latter by analyzing the learned representations of three spatial datasets (world, US, NYC places) and three temporal datasets (historical figures, artworks, news headlines) in the Llama-2 family of models."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\nThe main discoveries include:\n\n1. "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "LLMs learn linear representations of space and time across multiple scales."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n2. "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "These representations are robust to prompting variations and unified across different entity types (e.g. cities and landmarks)."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n3. "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In addition, they identify individual \"space neurons\" and \"time neurons\" that reliably encode spatial and temporal coordinates."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n4. "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "While further investigation is needed, their results suggest modern LLMs learn rich spatiotemporal representations of the real world and possess basic ingredients of a world model."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Paper History\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper was first submitted on Tue, 3 Oct 2023, with the latest revision (v3) on Mon, 4 Mar 2024."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## TL;DR\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Probing for spatial and temporal features in Llama-2 models."
      }
